The assault case against EFF leaders Julius Malema and Mbuyiseni Ndlozi has been postponed to 01 July. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - The assault case against EFF leaders Julius Malema and Mbuyiseni Ndlozi has been postponed to 1 July. They are facing a common assault charge for allegedly attacking Lieutenant Colonel Johannes Venter at Winnie Mandela's funeral in 2018. During his testimony, Malema said they tried to reach out to Venter to find ways to resolve the issue. READ: Malema, Ndlozi discharge application dismissed He claims Venter did not attend the meeting but instead opted to take the Afriforum route. Meanwhile, the Randburg Magistrates Court dismissed the discharge application brought by the duo. Watch the video above for more details.